summary: Comprehensive testing of Founder Intelligence Platform MVP - Backend APIs fully functional, frontend authentication issue identified

authentication_issues.issue: Session cookie not being recognized properly in frontend, causing authenticated users to be redirected to landing page
authentication_issues.symptoms: Direct navigation to protected routes (/dashboard, /upload, etc.) redirects to landing page even with valid session cookie
authentication_issues.root_cause: Possible cookie domain/path mismatch or HttpOnly/Secure/SameSite policy issues

passed_tests: Auth API with Bearer token authentication
Metrics computation with composite scores (Growth, Efficiency, PMF, Scalability, Capital Efficiency)
AI insights generation using GPT-5.2 (strategic insights, red flags, opportunities)
AI narrative generation using GPT-5.2 (traction statements, VC emails, summaries)
Landing page rendering with Sign in with Google buttons
Feature cards display on landing page
Frontend authentication works when navigated through internal links (first test run)
action_item_for_main_agent: Fix frontend authentication cookie handling - session cookies are not being properly recognized, causing authenticated users to be redirected to landing page. All backend APIs work perfectly. Issue likely in cookie domain/path settings or HttpOnly/Secure/SameSite policies in browser environment.
success_percentage: Backend: 100% (13/13 tests passed), Frontend: 70% (authentication flow broken for direct navigation)
